		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Zen and the Art of Pulling<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sat, Dec 16th 6:27 PM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=97699123731554&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=97699123731554&num=2&page=&post=1&replyto=97699123731554"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=97699123731554></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=7899"><span id=Scholar>Chimi</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>18 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.40]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Chimi&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I have a friend of mine, a dwarf pally who in his rise through knighthood, has become quite the master-puller. As soon as the stubby cavalier enters Norrath, he gets anywhere from 10 to 20 tells asking if he wants to group, he's made it on quite a few friends lists because of his knack for pulling. So one day, while frequenting the dwarven bordellos, he imparted his wisdom to me.<br><br>-1. Know Your Group<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;  Know what your boys are capable of. Know how much you can bring in and know that everyone has a grip on their role in the party.<br><br>-2. Assist<br>    Know that everyone has /assist hotkeyed and that they use it. Very Important. This way everyone is targeted on the same Mob. This allows your enchanter to mez, and keep those extra 3 or 4 Mobs you brought in off your back until you've dealt with the one you currently pummeling.<br><br>-3. Stream Pulling<br>    Know that downtime is bored time, know that your group is efficent (i.e. doesn't nuke when no nuke needed, medding in combat when tanks got everything under control). Don't wait for all the Mob's to be dead before your off to pulling again. Announce that your pulling, this should key the cleric to slap you with a quick heal before you bolt, and then bring some more Mob's back. A-B-P! Always Be Pulling. I said it before, I'll say it again. Always be Pulling. Good, well balanced groups can handle the constant stream of Mob's you so happily bring in. That being said, don't be a complete idiot. If you just uber-pulled and the party has low mana & health, take a breather. But idealy, you should be pulling Mob's that give you the most xp to the least amount of downtime. Constant blues & yellow could be more efficent than that tempting big red you see.<br><br>-4. Splitting Pulls<br>    First get to level 17. Then max out feign death ( should be at 90 maxed out at lvl 17). Then proceed in down yonder hill and pull your brains out. Feign death is pure pull control. You pull too many Mob's? Feign Death. You pull too big of a red? Feign Death. You pull annoying, no xp greenies. Feign Death. But the real beauty is in the first scenerio, too many Mob's. You waltz in the middle of 8 pissed off Mob's. Aggro them. Run away from spawn point. Feign Death. Those Mob's will slowly break apart, one after the other heading back to spawn point. Get up. Re-aggro, this time pulling only 6 Mob's as 2 went back to spawn point. Run. Feign death. Let 2 more leave. Re-aggro. You get the point. This allows you to control how many Mobs you pull in. Sweet and simple.<br><br>-5 Information Highway.<br>   Communication. Very important in group harmony. It all starts with you. When you pull, let them know what you're pulling. Let them know when you're pulling. Let them know when you've pulled too much and gotta zone. Get constant mana updates from your casters. Let the healers know when you're mending. Have a full set of hotkeys setup for pulling. Here's my Hotkey setup:<br>     --1 Inc1 (/g Inc %T)<br>     --2 Inc2 (/g Inc 2 Mobs, %T targeted)<br>     --3 Inc3 (/g Inc 3 Mobs, %T targeted)<br>     --4 Inc4 (/g Inc 4 Mobs, %T targeted)<br>     --5 Inc5 (/g Inc 5 Mobs, %T targeted)<br>     --6 Inc6 (/g Inc 6 Mobs, %T targeted)<br>     --7 FD   (the almighty Feign death key)<br>     --8 Range Attack (you didnt ignore thrown<br>                       weapon skill, did you?)<br>     --9 Zone (/g OMG! Uber pull! Gotta Zone!)<br>     -10 Pull (/g pulling)<br><br>When I pull more than one Mob I try to target on the one I want dead first (i.e. "Inc 3 Mobs, Orc Priest targeted). It'll let the group know which Mob is priority one before you bring them all in.<br><br><br>Well that about covers it. Learn it. Know it. Live it. Anyone spot anything I may have overlooked, let me know. Good luck and happy pulling!<br><br>-Chimi, also the author of "Zen and the art of pulling out".<br><br><br><br><br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
